<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-23-1067 </DOCNO><TEXT>Causes and consequences of the greenhouse effect are discussed. Combustionof fossil fuels and increasing deforestation cause an increase of CO/sub2/ in the atmosphere. This results in rising of temperature on earth.Some positive and negative consequences are discussed, but the effectsof the greenhouse effect are uncertain for climate and agriculture. Framedwithin this article the carbon cycle is explained and attention is paidto the rise of the sea level as a consequence of the rising temperature.Finally future policy with regard to the greenhouse effect is illustratedby some greenhouse-scenarios. 8 figs., 6 refs.</TEXT></DOC>